    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for your comment posted on the NHS website and please accept our apologies that you have been unable to contact Ward 37, Manchester Royal Infirmary and the main switchboard. We are aware that it is extremely difficult for families and patients during the visiting restrictions due to Covid-19 and although we note that you recognised how busy our staff members are, your concerns have been escalated to the Lead Nurse so that they can look into the reasons why your call is not being answered. Therefore it would be helpful to have further information from you regarding this and we would appreciate it if you could contact us on the number below to provide more detail.

Virtual Visiting has been established to support patients and families during Covid-19 and this enables video calls to take place with patients, with the support of the Patient Experience and Volunteers team and can be booked by calling 0161 701 8956 Monday â€“ Friday between 9.00am and 12 noon to arrange an afternoon appointment. 

If you would like to discuss your concerns with us in more detail, please feel free to contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service on 0161 276 8686 or by emailing pals@mft.nhs.uk quoting reference number PO20/0059. 

The Patient Experience Team &lt;/CommentText&gt;
